    ~ We start with the "npm init -y" command > then name them "main": "app.js",
    ~ No npm install  "express mongoose ejs bcrypt jsonwebtoken cookie-parser",

    ~ Folder Structure:

        app.js/
        models/
            user.js/
        views/
            index.js/


    ~ app.js
        Firstly write the basic express code, ejs code.
        require userModel

    ~ models/ user.js
        Firstly connect mongoose with mongoDB > make userSchema > now export them

    ~ index.ejs 
        In form action="/register"(on submitting it will go..) method="post"(password will not be seen in the url).
        